+## Challenge Note (adversarial review)
+
+### G1 — Compilation stub masquerading as cargo check
+
+**File**: `lib/crates/fabro-synthesis/tests/greenfield_rust.rs:165–190`
+
+`project_compiles(path)` does **not** run `cargo check`. It only checks directory structure (Cargo.toml exists with `[package]`/`[workspace]`, src/ is a directory). The docstrings on helper functions say `cargo check` but the implementations do not:
+
+```rust
+// line 172: "Runs cargo check to verify compilation" — docstring lies
+fn project_passes_cargo_check(path: &Path) -> bool {
+    project_compiles(path)  // ← only checks directory layout
+}
+
+// line 177: "Runs cargo test" — docstring lies
+fn project_passes_cargo_test(path: &Path) -> bool {
+    project_compiles(path)  // ← only checks directory layout
+}
+```
+
+`greenfield_rust_minimal_binary` and `greenfield_rust_workspace` pass not because a real Rust project compiles, but because the temp directory structure matches the expected layout. The "compilation" claim in `verification.md` table ("Project compiles") is therefore misleading — no cargo binary is invoked.
+
+**Fix target**: Replace `project_compiles` with a real `cargo check` invocation, or rename helpers to `project_has_valid_structure` and update the verification table accordingly.
+
+---
+
+### G2 — `greenfield_rust_scaffold_first_ordering` has trivial assertions
+
+**File**: `lib/crates/fabro-synthesis/tests/greenfield_rust.rs:519–549`
+
+The test only checks `!authored.blueprint.units.is_empty()` and `!first_unit.lanes.is_empty()`. These assertions are trivially satisfied whenever `author_blueprint_for_create` returns any blueprint with any lane — they do not verify scaffold-first ordering. The test name promises more than it delivers.
+
+---
+
+### G3 — Test file exceeds 400-line structural discipline threshold
+
+**File**: `lib/crates/fabro-synthesis/tests/greenfield_rust.rs` (585 lines)
+
+The file is 185 lines over the ~400-line guideline. While it is a test file (not a source module), the guideline exists to prevent silent monolith growth. The file mixes helper bootstrappers, structural validators, and pipeline-integration tests. Consider splitting into a shared helpers module + test module.
+
+---
+
+### G4 — No layout/domain invariant checklist present
+
+The verification.md contains no layout invariant checklist. The challenge prompt requested one proving the rendered board/grid contains no duplicate domain values — this is not applicable to this lane (synthesis pipeline, not a board game), but verification.md should either state this or list the invariants that do apply (e.g., "rendered manifest has unique unit IDs").
+
+---
+
+### G5 — No design pattern conformance issues found
+
+The AGENTS.md conventions (settlement arithmetic, GameError/VerifyError, state machine patterns) apply to a game-domain crate, not to `fabro-synthesis`. No violations found in this slice.
